body.name: DaVinci Autumn 4-in-1 Convertible Mini Crib in Slate, Greenguard Gold Certified
features: GREENGUARD GOLD CERTIFIED: This product has undergone rigorous scientific testing for over 10,000 chemical emissions and VOCs. It contributes to cleaner indoor air, creating a healthier environment for your baby to sleep, play, and grow

GROWS WITH BABY: Four adjustable mattress positions that can be lowered as your baby begins to sit and stand. Easily converts to a mini toddler bed, daybed, and twin-size bed (mini toddler kit #M20399 and twin/full-size kit #M5789 sold separately)
QUALITY MATERIAL: Made of solid sustainable New Zealand pinewood and TSCA compliant engineered wood
FOR YOUR BABY'S SAFETY: Say goodbye to toxic chemicals! Finished in a non-toxic multi-step painting process and lead and phthalate safe
COMPLETE THE LOOK: Shop Autumn 4-Drawer Changer Dresser (#M4355), Autumn Bookcase / Hutch (#M4309) and Jayden 6-Drawer Double Wide Dresser (#M5966) for a coordinated nursery
body.description: The space-saving design of the Autumn 4-in-1 Convertible Mini Crib will bring both delight and a touch of traditional appeal to any nursery. This mini-sized version of our full-sized Autumn 4-in-1 Crib has the same clean and strong lines with refined raised molding on its high headboard. The Autumn grows with your child with its four different mattress height positions and converts into a mini toddler bed, daybed, and twin-size bed to grow with your child (conversion kits sold separately).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great mini crib!!
reviews.reviewText: While this product did have a scuff/hole on it upon unpacking, it was just on the bottom, inside panel thing so it’s not a big deal to me because it’s hidden. I absolutely love this mini crib! I was rather upset that I didn’t get to have a full size crib since we are room sharing with our new addition, but this crib definitely made up for it. It’s super cute and good quality, but also it’s small enough so she has her own area in our room. It was pretty easy to put together with my husbands help so that is definitely a plus. My only thing is that while there is technically a mattress included, it’s VERY thin (like, 1 1/2 in.) so I’d you are wanting something bigger you’ll have to order that separate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Mini Crib
reviews.reviewText: Took my husband about 1 hour to assemble all by himself. Easy, uncomplicated instructions. Packaged well so that no parts were damaged during shipping. It shipped faster than expexted as well, which was a nice surprise. Exactly as advertised, beautiful, sturdy, compact crib. Just slightly smaller than the pack and play we were using. My 4 month old sleeps very well in this. Very happy this purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is a seriously beautiful piece of furniture.
reviews.reviewText: First of all, **this is NOT an incentivized review**.Second of all, this crib is gorgeous and shockingly solid for the price. I was set on a standard sized, solid wood, beautiful crib that cost a couple hundred dollars more, but finally decided to give in and get this thing thanks to the seemingly never-ending inflation plaguing us all. It’s a decision I don’t regret, and I really hope my baby can stay in this for a long time.The crib has a “lodge” look, reminiscent of a warm and welcoming cabin in the woods. I purchased woodland themed sheets to go with it, and they enhance the look. As another reviewer stated, the wood is soft, so be careful with it during assembly, or if you have to move it. If you can do this, it should serve you well and add some charm to your home!One more thing - we keep this crib right next to our bed, since our baby is still very little. We had a bedside bassinet at first, but if we had another baby we’d probably put her in this crib right from the start.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So glad I picked this
reviews.reviewText: This mini crib is perfect. I am pregnant with my 3rd baby and did not have much room for a regular sized crib. I was so worried this would look too small or doll sized. It most certainly does not. It’s the perfect size and color. I’m so happy with my purchase. I am 33 weeks and it took me alone about an hour to assemble. Very easy. I recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars An affordable mini crib for parents on a budget
reviews.reviewText: The instructions for the DaVinci Autumn 4-in-1 convertible crib were not the best but was able to follow them with only minor confusion. Overall sturdiness seems good--had one minor flaw in the headboard, a crack that existed or may have occurred when fitting pieces together. It didn't impact integrity, aesthetics, or pose a risk to baby, so we didn't go through the hassle of unassembling/returning the product.Overall, we are happy with this mini crib, it fits our needs and space, and it was much more affordable than other cribs on the market.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this mini crib!!
reviews.reviewText: Super cute mini crib, and I feel like i got a really good deal! It was very easy to assemble and took maybe 30 minutes for my husband and I to put it together. It felt very sturdy once we had everything together. This crib came with a mattress even though I didn’t purchase the added mattress option, however the mattress is super thin, maybe 1” thick and not firm at all, I would suggest purchasing a 3” firm mini crib or pack n play mattress for it like I did. I actually stacked the 3” mattress I had on top the mattress the crib came with and put a crib sheet over them and now I have a 4” firm crib mattress!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Esta súper bonita la cuna llego en perfectas condiciones ideal para espacios pequeños muy cómoda y bonita

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 22, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful, Tall & Sturdy but buy an additional mattress.
reviews.reviewText: Beautiful little crib! I chose this one because my son was 1 already and this was the taller than most mini cribs out there. Although he actually never spent one night in it it was not an eyesore in our bedroom (until it became a laundry basket lol). It's very sturdy, nice looking and roomy for a small crib. The mattress that comes with it is very thin so we just put a thicker one on top of it.

Nos ha llegado en perfectas condiciones, súper fácil de montar, estoy embarazada de 7m y lo he podido montar sola. Tiene un tamaño en mi opinión perfecto, para los que no queréis comprar un Moises para los primeros meses, esta opción creo que por su tamaño podremos usarla hasta año y medio, dependerá de su peso. La colchoneta es muy fina, hace falta comprar un colchón, acabo de pedir el Dream On Me Mattress ya que he leído alguna reseña de clientes que compraron una mini cuna Da Vinci y les sirvió perfecto este colchón, a ver qué tal... Saludos!

Consideró que es una cuna que cumplió con mis expectativas y mis necesidades. Si considero que armarla me fue un poco complicado, pero la verdad es que tanto los materiales, así como su terminado es de excelente calidad. Altamente recomendable para un hogar pequeño

Llego a tiempo, bien protegida, el material de calidad, madera se siente resistente y fue fácil armarla (entre dos es mejor) muy recomendada 👍🏽👍🏽 Se ve super bella y con un tinte elegante (es algo pequeña)
Sin duda excelente cuna, es del tamaño de una de viaje perfecta para un departamento, facilmente te puede servir hasta los 2 años de tu bebe. la calidad del materia es buena nada de mdf o acerrin.

reviews.reviewTitle: Bonita pero cuidado con los dedos al armar.
reviews.reviewText: Me encantó la cuna, fácil de armar, bonito diseño. Pero los largueros de la base del colchón son filosos y pueden cortar al armar, me hubiera gustado saberlo antes. (Los largueros no pueden ser tocados por el bebé así que no es grave).
